# Styling Guidelines

The project uses Tailwind CSS for styling components.

## Styling Structure

- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind configuration
- [postcss.config.js](mdc:postcss.config.js) - PostCSS configuration for Tailwind
- [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css) - Global CSS styles
- [src/App.css](mdc:src/App.css) - App-specific CSS styles

## Tailwind Conventions

- Use responsive prefixes for different screen sizes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Use dark mode variant (`dark:`) for dark theme styles
- Use state variants like `hover:`, `focus:`, `active:` for interactive elements
- Use group and peer modifiers for parent-child interactions

## Example Tailwind Classes

```jsx
// Responsive design
<div className="text-center sm:text-left md:text-right"></div>

// Dark mode
<div className="bg-white text-black dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-white"></div>

// Interactive states
<button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 focus:ring-2"></button>

// Group interaction
<div className="group">
  <span className="text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-500"></span>
</div>
```
